==English==
===Etymology===
{{der|en|la|xyris||iris}} (see {{m|mul|Xyris}}) + {{af|en|-id}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈzaɪɹɪd/}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# Any of several [[North American]] [[plant]]s, of the genus ''[[Xyris]]'', resembling [[sedge]]s.
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Wildflowers of south-eastern Australia|page=48|author=Elizabeth Conebere|year=1987|passage=Its family, Xyridaceae, is closely allied to the lilies: '''xyrids''' have three stamens, while lilies generally have six.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Early Events in Monocot Evolution|page=318|author=Paul Wilkin|year=2013|passage=These four subdivisions correspond to groups sometimes referred to as the cyperids, '''xyrids''', restiids and graminids, respectively (Linder and Rudall, 2005), except that Hydatellaceae was originally included among the '''xyrids''', and since has been removed from the monocots (Saarela et al., 2007).}}
